@thnk2wn Here's a function you can put in your profile to make Sudo work with Powershell cmdlets and aliases, with `sudo !!` functioning like in Bash thrown in:

```
function sudo
{
	if($args[0] -eq '!!')
	{
		sudo $((Get-History ((Get-History).Count))[0].CommandLine) 
		return
	}
	. $(which sudo) pwsh -NoProfile -Command ". $PROFILE *> /dev/null; $args"
}
```

Probably won't help you with `Update-Help` though.
